You should override each call you are interested in, copying out the data you need. Then within `onComplete()`/`onCancel()` you store the data to the database. `onComplete()`/`onCancel()` is always the end of the RPC (although realize that sending can occur after a cancellation, because processing the cancel is racy; anything after `onCancel()` is discarded by grpc).

You will be creating a (forwarding) ServerCall and a (forwarding) ServerCall.Listener. To store the data in &quot;one place&quot;, you can simply have one of your objects reference the other one (e.g., a nested class).

Note that it is _really_ important to make a full copy of the `Metadata`, since it is not a thread-safe object.

